# Copy to .env.local for local dev, or set these in the Vercel project's
# Environment Variables. Every var is optional — with none set the app fetches
# live from the public LeetCode API and skips the Supabase catalog. Only the
# NEXT_PUBLIC_* vars below are read by the app at runtime.

# LeetCode API base URL. Defaults to the hosted instance when unset.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_LEETCODE_API_BASE=https://leetcode-api-pied.vercel.app

# Supabase project (read-only catalog). Set both to read the persisted
# `problems` table instead of the live API. When absent the app falls back
# to the live API (see lib/supabase.ts).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=sb_publishable_...
# Legacy anon JWT also accepted in place of the publishable key:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...

# Service-role key — used ONLY by the offline sync scripts/Edge Function
# (supabase/), never by the app. Do not add this to Vercel.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJ...
